what does the the common tongue twister seek to teach in its saying and its twistingness

Tongue twisters are often used to help develop speech and language skills such as pronunciation, clarity, and speed. They are also used to promote oral motor skills and coordination of the mouth muscles, which can be helpful for people with speech impediments or challenges. Additionally, some tongue twisters may be used for entertainment purposes or as a fun challenge among friends. The twisting nature of tongue twisters forces the speaker to focus on enunciating each word carefully and quickly, which can improve one's overall speech abilities.
